WEBVTT

00:08.166 --> 00:10.083
[Ray] Previously
on  Ray Donovan...

00:10.083 --> 00:14.208
I know what I'm asking you
to do is dangerous,

00:14.208 --> 00:16.000
but I'm out of options.

00:16.000 --> 00:18.041
I got nowhere else
to turn but family.

00:18.041 --> 00:19.542
I don't expect your help.

00:19.542 --> 00:21.500
God knows I don't deserve it.

00:21.500 --> 00:24.000
If any of you want to walk
out of this room right now,

00:24.000 --> 00:24.208
I wouldn't blame you.

00:26.458 --> 00:27.333
[Ray]
Fuck you, Frank.

00:27.333 --> 00:29.667
You want Sokolov,
we do it my way.

00:29.667 --> 00:32.125
Wear the fucking shirt, Ray,
or you're done.

00:32.125 --> 00:33.709
Arrest me.

00:33.709 --> 00:35.583
- You want to win this fight?
- Yeah.

00:35.583 --> 00:36.625
Win it.

00:36.625 --> 00:38.166
[referee]
Time!

00:38.166 --> 00:41.917
Our business is over,
Mr. Donovan.

00:41.917 --> 00:44.542
You are a very foolish man.

00:44.542 --> 00:48.208
Hello, friend.
Get in.

00:48.208 --> 00:50.250
[man] speaking Russian

00:50.250 --> 00:51.917
Here you go, buddy.

00:51.917 --> 00:52.500
Good, now walk away.
You don't want to see this.

00:52.500 --> 00:54.625
[gunshot]

00:54.625 --> 00:55.792
What the fuck is this?

00:55.792 --> 00:58.875
Cocaine, heroin, fentanyl.

00:58.875 --> 01:00.834
The art came in,
they loaded it up,

01:00.834 --> 01:02.291
the art went back out.

01:02.291 --> 01:05.375
You'll find Sokolov's body
in Anaheim.

01:05.375 --> 01:07.542
Nice work, Frank.

01:07.542 --> 01:10.166
Looks like you brought down
another crime boss.

01:10.166 --> 01:13.041
It's fucking great
to be a Donovan.

01:13.041 --> 01:16.041
[Abby] Yesterday I thought
everything was over.

01:16.041 --> 01:19.291
I thought that we'd never
be able to come home again.

01:19.291 --> 01:20.750
Now, look.

01:20.750 --> 01:22.542
We got a fresh start, Ray.

01:22.542 --> 01:23.667
I told you everything
would work out,

01:23.667 --> 01:24.834
didn't I?

01:24.834 --> 01:27.291
Yeah, you did.

01:27.291 --> 01:29.875
Don't you ever fucking doubt me
again, Ray Donovan.

01:29.875 --> 01:32.250
No one can touch us.

01:32.250 --> 01:35.291
♪ dramatic music ♪

01:35.291 --> 01:39.417
♪♪♪

01:49.417 --> 01:52.500
♪ Cat Power's "Sea of Love" ♪

01:52.500 --> 01:57.375
♪♪♪

02:01.917 --> 02:03.583
♪ Come with me ♪

02:03.583 --> 02:04.917
[Mickey]
All right.

02:04.917 --> 02:06.625
♪ My love ♪

02:06.625 --> 02:08.125
[Mickey]
All right.

02:08.125 --> 02:10.625
♪ To the sea ♪

02:10.625 --> 02:14.125
♪ The sea of love ♪

02:14.125 --> 02:17.834
♪ I want to tell you... ♪

02:17.834 --> 02:19.500
[woman]
Morning, Mickey.

02:19.500 --> 02:21.959
I called in an order
for ten boutonnieres.

02:21.959 --> 02:23.250
Great, I'll get those for you.

02:23.250 --> 02:24.792
Is someone getting married?

02:24.792 --> 02:26.959
Yeah, one of my sons
tomorrow afternoon.

02:26.959 --> 02:29.417
That's wonderful.

02:29.417 --> 02:30.917
Yeah, it's a happy occasion.

02:30.917 --> 02:34.792
♪♪♪

02:34.792 --> 02:37.625
Happy occasion.

02:37.625 --> 02:40.792
♪ Do you remember ♪

02:40.792 --> 02:44.583
♪ When we met? ♪

02:44.583 --> 02:46.750
♪ That's the day ♪

02:46.750 --> 02:48.917
♪ I knew you were my pet ♪

02:48.917 --> 02:54.542
♪ I want to tell you ♪

02:54.542 --> 02:55.959
♪♪♪

02:55.959 --> 03:00.166
♪ How much ♪

03:00.166 --> 03:03.041
♪ I love you ♪

03:03.041 --> 03:05.333
Stay here.

03:05.333 --> 03:06.875
Don't chew nothing.

03:07.667 --> 03:13.667
♪♪♪

03:13.667 --> 03:16.667
♪ Come with me ♪

03:16.667 --> 03:20.500
♪ My love ♪

03:20.500 --> 03:22.500
♪ To the sea ♪

03:22.500 --> 03:25.125
♪ The sea of love ♪

03:25.125 --> 03:30.917
♪ I want to tell you ♪

03:32.250 --> 03:36.709
♪ How much ♪

03:36.709 --> 03:41.625
♪ I love you ♪

03:43.000 --> 03:47.250
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

03:47.250 --> 03:49.750
[door opens]

03:49.750 --> 03:53.542
♪♪♪

03:53.542 --> 03:56.333
Raymond Donovan?

04:04.792 --> 04:09.083
[man whistles]

04:09.083 --> 04:11.792
So...

04:11.792 --> 04:13.792
you want to tell me
what happened?

04:13.792 --> 04:17.083
It's in the file, right?

04:17.083 --> 04:18.917
In your words.

04:18.917 --> 04:20.750
I got in a fight.

04:20.750 --> 04:23.125
I see that.

04:23.125 --> 04:24.083
Why did you get in a fight?

04:24.083 --> 04:28.667
Ah, some stupid stuff,
you know?

04:28.667 --> 04:30.000
My family.

04:30.000 --> 04:32.583
- Stupid stuff?
- Mm-hmm.

04:32.583 --> 04:33.834
Like what?

04:33.834 --> 04:36.000
Oh, family thing.
Brothers.

04:36.000 --> 04:38.959
A family thing

04:38.959 --> 04:40.625
that led to
you getting arrested.

04:40.625 --> 04:43.250
Yeah, well, the cops
should've never been there.

04:43.250 --> 04:44.583
But they were.

04:44.583 --> 04:45.917
And you're here, so...

04:45.917 --> 04:48.709
In your words.

04:48.709 --> 04:50.667
[distorted crying]
Dad, stop!

04:50.667 --> 04:55.333
[crying]

04:55.333 --> 04:56.834
Stop!

04:59.750 --> 05:02.792
[Dr. Brogan] Are you
gonna answer my question?

05:02.792 --> 05:05.625
I told you.

05:05.625 --> 05:07.834
It was a family thing.

05:07.834 --> 05:12.000
Your 19-year-old daughter
called the police.

05:12.000 --> 05:15.458
Your brother and your father
were hospitalized.

05:15.458 --> 05:19.709
And what kind of
family thing is that?

05:21.959 --> 05:24.375
It says you were intoxicated
during this family thing.

05:24.375 --> 05:25.834
We all were.

05:25.834 --> 05:27.959
- It was in a bar, so...
- Mm-hmm.

05:27.959 --> 05:30.125
You think you have
a drinking problem?

05:30.125 --> 05:31.542
No.

05:34.166 --> 05:36.458
Have you ever been through
any kind of therapy before?

05:36.458 --> 05:39.667
Yeah.
My wife.

05:39.667 --> 05:43.166
How long were you
in couples therapy?

05:43.166 --> 05:45.125
About 10 to 15 minutes.

05:45.125 --> 05:49.709
Why were you in couples therapy
for only 15 minutes?

05:51.542 --> 05:54.542
My wife said
what she wanted to say, and...

05:54.542 --> 05:55.750
we worked it out, so...

05:55.750 --> 05:57.750
I left.

05:57.750 --> 06:00.583
Yeah.

06:00.959 --> 06:02.166
[sighs]

06:02.166 --> 06:04.500
Fill this out for me.

06:04.500 --> 06:07.583
Bring it back before
the end of business today.

06:15.208 --> 06:17.542
Look, I get it.
I, uh--

06:17.542 --> 06:18.834
I-I-I know why I'm here.

06:18.834 --> 06:20.208
I'm a grown man.
I shouldn't--

06:20.208 --> 06:21.875
I shouldn't be fighting
in bars.

06:21.875 --> 06:24.208
I--You know, it--
it's not the kind of thing

06:24.208 --> 06:26.041
that's gonna happen again.

06:28.041 --> 06:30.125
Is there some other way
we can work this out?

06:30.125 --> 06:33.417
Twelve sessions...

06:33.417 --> 06:35.917
completed in 90 days.

06:35.917 --> 06:37.458
Do that,

06:37.458 --> 06:40.375
follow the rules
of your probation,

06:40.375 --> 06:42.667
and you will have fulfilled
your obligations to the court.

06:44.750 --> 06:48.792
Come back in two days...
same time.

06:48.792 --> 06:50.583
We'll pick up
where we left off.

07:01.750 --> 07:03.667
[Damon] Yo, Terry,
you okay in there?

07:03.667 --> 07:05.125
Just tying a tie.

07:05.125 --> 07:06.750
[Damon]
Need any help with that?

07:06.750 --> 07:09.417
Fuck off.
I'm fine.

07:20.000 --> 07:21.250
What do you think?

07:21.250 --> 07:23.792
Mm, man, you look fresh.

07:23.792 --> 07:25.208
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

07:25.208 --> 07:26.583
Does it fit good?

07:26.583 --> 07:30.083
How about we lose
the hat this time?

07:30.083 --> 07:31.667
Yo, take off the hat, Ter.

07:37.125 --> 07:39.166
Oh. Wow.

07:39.166 --> 07:41.583
- [exhales deeply]
- What happened?

07:41.583 --> 07:45.250
I had surgery
for my Parkinson's.

07:45.250 --> 07:46.875
They put a pacemaker
in his brain

07:46.875 --> 07:47.625
and drilled holes
into his head.

07:47.625 --> 07:49.917
You want to
see something cool?

07:49.917 --> 07:51.959
What?

07:51.959 --> 07:54.375
Show her, Ter.

08:05.125 --> 08:08.125
♪ soft music ♪

08:08.125 --> 08:10.500
♪♪♪

08:10.500 --> 08:12.667
My God.

08:12.667 --> 08:14.959
♪ somber music ♪

08:14.959 --> 08:15.875
You--you okay?

08:15.875 --> 08:18.125
Yeah.

08:18.125 --> 08:21.667
♪♪♪

08:21.667 --> 08:24.834
I got to go.

08:24.834 --> 08:26.709
So can you get this ready
by tomorrow?

08:26.709 --> 08:28.417
Yes, Mr. Donovan.

08:28.417 --> 08:29.667
Damon, you got to
get yourself fitted up.

08:29.667 --> 08:32.166
Make sure you
look good for Maureen.

08:32.166 --> 08:34.417
All right.

08:35.542 --> 08:38.625
♪ Latin dubstep music ♪

08:38.625 --> 08:43.208
♪♪♪

08:43.208 --> 08:44.667
[grunts]

08:46.458 --> 08:48.500
Aquí.

08:48.500 --> 08:53.542
♪♪♪

08:53.542 --> 08:55.583
[groans]

08:55.583 --> 08:57.166
Ah!

08:57.166 --> 08:59.166
[grunting, laughs]

08:59.166 --> 09:03.542
♪♪♪

09:03.542 --> 09:04.208
Come on, let's see
what you got.

09:04.208 --> 09:07.000
[roars]

09:09.166 --> 09:11.000
[giggles]

09:21.125 --> 09:23.291
[giggles]

09:26.208 --> 09:28.792
[shouting]

09:32.709 --> 09:34.041
God damn it, Brenda!

09:34.041 --> 09:36.542
It's Brendan.

09:36.542 --> 09:38.250
You got to take
two steps forward.

09:38.250 --> 09:40.250
I know.
I fucking know.

09:40.250 --> 09:42.875
- [man] shouting in Spanish
- [cell phone ringing]

09:42.875 --> 09:44.375
[soft groaning]

09:44.375 --> 09:46.083
By the time they hit her
the fourth time,

09:46.083 --> 09:47.208
I need you back in the ring
with the clothesline.

09:47.208 --> 09:49.583
I got it.

09:49.583 --> 09:51.166
Look, I-I got to get
to work.

09:51.166 --> 09:53.375
The audition's at eight.

09:53.375 --> 09:55.083
Let's try not to fuck this up.

09:55.083 --> 09:56.125
[man]
Ayúdame.

09:56.125 --> 09:58.583
[man groaning]

09:58.583 --> 10:00.583
♪♪♪

10:00.583 --> 10:03.667
[men] speaking Spanish

10:03.667 --> 10:06.500
♪♪♪

10:06.500 --> 10:10.542
Come on, let's get back to work.

10:13.375 --> 10:16.542
[train squeaking]

10:18.417 --> 10:21.542
[air hissing]

10:23.500 --> 10:26.583
[siren wailing, car horn honks
in the distance]

10:32.625 --> 10:34.875
[siren wailing in the distance]

10:38.125 --> 10:41.417
I got the boutonnieres.

10:41.417 --> 10:42.500
I told you not to
bring the fucking dog

10:42.500 --> 10:44.291
in here anymore, Mick.

10:44.291 --> 10:47.792
It gets lonely, too.

10:47.792 --> 10:50.500
Beckett.

10:50.500 --> 10:52.625
[Mickey] Maureen's aunt
is a 12-stepper,

10:52.625 --> 10:55.083
so Terry told me to order
more nonalcoholic beer,

10:55.083 --> 10:57.125
which I did.

10:57.125 --> 10:59.041
What's that?

10:59.041 --> 11:02.208
Nothing.
You got a pen?

11:06.625 --> 11:08.125
What you doing, Mick?

11:08.125 --> 11:09.875
Writing a screenplay.

11:09.875 --> 11:10.333
It's gonna be a killer.

11:10.333 --> 11:11.750
Ooh, writing.

11:11.750 --> 11:14.500
I didn't even know
you could read.

11:14.500 --> 11:17.917
And I didn't know gas stations
sold women's clothes.

11:19.667 --> 11:21.500
You got a B
on your health inspection.

11:21.500 --> 11:22.542
Hmm.

11:22.542 --> 11:24.333
That manager you got--

11:24.333 --> 11:26.333
he's serving people sandwiches
on moldy bread.

11:26.333 --> 11:27.750
- You got to dump him.
- Abby hired him.

11:27.750 --> 11:29.542
I told you I was
a front-of-the-house guy.

11:29.542 --> 11:31.959
You wanted me to cook.

11:31.959 --> 11:33.917
So, action, meet consequence.

11:35.667 --> 11:38.667
You're losing 20,000 a month.

11:38.667 --> 11:40.583
Sell now, stop the bleeding.

11:40.583 --> 11:44.208
I got a lead
on some self-storage units.

11:44.208 --> 11:46.542
- I'm not selling, Harriet.
- Oh, fine.

11:46.542 --> 11:49.291
[Harriet] Just burn the money.
Why the fuck you pay me?

11:49.291 --> 11:50.208
All right.

11:50.208 --> 11:52.542
I'll bite.

11:52.542 --> 11:54.750
Oh, you're interested, huh?

11:54.750 --> 11:57.166
[Mickey] Well,
it's sophisticated.

11:57.166 --> 11:58.792
Maybe I can dumb it down
for you.

11:58.792 --> 12:01.500
[whiskey pours]

12:01.500 --> 12:03.667
[Mickey]
The lead character, Michael--

12:03.667 --> 12:05.500
he's a tough Boston dockworker,

12:05.500 --> 12:09.125
lost his wife,
raising four kids on his own.

12:09.125 --> 12:10.875
And when one of
the kids gets sick,

12:10.875 --> 12:13.041
Michael turns
to robbing banks

12:13.041 --> 12:14.875
to take care
of the little one,

12:14.875 --> 12:17.500
'cause that little sweet girl

12:17.500 --> 12:19.291
needs a heart transplant.

12:19.291 --> 12:19.750
[Harriet]
Does she die?

12:19.750 --> 12:20.667
[Mickey]
Maybe.

12:20.667 --> 12:23.333
It's what you call
a tearjerker.

12:23.333 --> 12:26.917
No, she shouldn't die.
People wouldn't like that.

12:45.125 --> 12:47.250
Hey.
We're not open yet.

12:47.250 --> 12:48.750
[mumbles, sniffs]

12:53.792 --> 12:56.166
Hey, do--do I know you?

12:56.166 --> 12:57.542
Sloan Kettering.

12:57.542 --> 13:00.000
You're Bridget.

13:00.000 --> 13:02.000
Jake, right?

13:02.000 --> 13:03.917
Yeah.
[chuckles]

13:03.917 --> 13:06.917
- Well--well, uh, Smitty.
- Right.

13:06.917 --> 13:09.333
Uh, what are you doing here?
Do you live around here?

13:09.333 --> 13:12.834
No.

13:12.834 --> 13:15.458
So, um...

13:15.458 --> 13:17.667
what's--what's going on?

13:17.667 --> 13:19.625
I found out you work here.

13:19.625 --> 13:21.542
Okay.

13:21.542 --> 13:23.583
That's creepy.

13:23.583 --> 13:25.792
Oh, no, no, I'm--

13:25.792 --> 13:28.250
[chuckles] I'm just--
I'm just messing with you.

13:28.250 --> 13:29.250
I know it's weird.

13:29.250 --> 13:32.875
I-I called one of
the nurses at the hospital.

13:33.667 --> 13:37.417
Uh, how--how's your mom?

13:37.417 --> 13:39.208
She, um...

13:42.750 --> 13:44.625
[voice breaking]
She, um...

13:44.625 --> 13:48.375
Oh, my Go--I'm so sorry.

13:48.375 --> 13:50.458
Aw, man.

13:50.458 --> 13:52.583
I didn't mean to, um--

13:52.583 --> 13:54.125
I'm gonna go.
I'm sorry.

13:54.125 --> 13:55.500
Well, hey, can--can I--

13:55.500 --> 13:58.208
can I walk with you
for a second?

13:58.208 --> 13:58.834
♪ soft music ♪

13:58.834 --> 14:00.500
Don't you have to work?

14:00.500 --> 14:03.667
I got time.

14:03.667 --> 14:04.875
Okay.

14:04.875 --> 14:06.667
Yeah?

14:06.667 --> 14:11.667
♪♪♪

14:11.667 --> 14:14.208
I'm--I'm sorry, really.

14:14.208 --> 14:16.834
I-I can't even imagine
how you must feel.

14:16.834 --> 14:20.166
[inhales shakily]
Fuck.

14:20.166 --> 14:22.291
- Sorry.
- Yeah.

14:22.291 --> 14:23.417
Hey.

14:23.417 --> 14:25.000
Thank you.

14:25.000 --> 14:28.792
[exhales deeply,
sniffles, chuckles]

14:28.792 --> 14:30.625
Do--do you want to
go back to my apartment

14:30.625 --> 14:33.333
and--and get stoned?

14:33.333 --> 14:34.834
It's really close.
It's right by the IKEA.

14:34.834 --> 14:37.583
I'll get you
some Swedish meatballs.

14:37.583 --> 14:39.583
[laughs]

14:40.959 --> 14:43.041
Okay.

14:43.041 --> 14:44.709
♪♪♪

14:44.709 --> 14:46.208
Come on.

14:46.208 --> 14:49.000
♪♪♪

14:49.000 --> 14:52.208
[Mickey]
People like a good cry, Harriet.

14:52.208 --> 14:55.041
[Harriet]
Not over a dead kid.

14:55.041 --> 14:57.250
[Mickey]
What about this?

14:57.250 --> 15:00.542
There's a shootout in a bank.

15:00.542 --> 15:04.083
And, uh, Michael realizes that
he could die then and there.

15:04.083 --> 15:06.458
So he runs out, he covers
his heart with his hand.

15:06.458 --> 15:07.959
He gets shot,

15:07.959 --> 15:09.750
and his heart
goes to his little girl.

15:09.750 --> 15:11.875
[Mickey] That better?

15:11.875 --> 15:13.458
It was better when she died.

15:13.458 --> 15:15.083
- Why?
- Write what you know, Mick.

15:17.500 --> 15:20.125
You're late.

15:20.125 --> 15:21.208
I had wrestling practice.

15:21.208 --> 15:24.917
[Daryll, muffled]
Jay, brah, you and I both know

15:24.917 --> 15:27.750
that a rich, powerful
black man in America...

15:27.750 --> 15:29.875
It's a three-hole punch, Bunch.

15:29.875 --> 15:31.458
- [Daryll] Huh?
- Well, I didn't know.

15:31.458 --> 15:33.667
Yeah, you did,
'cause I told you last time.

15:33.667 --> 15:34.750
So take it back,
all right?

15:34.750 --> 15:37.875
White paper,
no three-hole punch.

15:37.875 --> 15:39.750
Make sure the coffee's
whole bean, not ground,

15:39.750 --> 15:42.000
'cause we have a grinder,
in case you don't remember.

15:42.000 --> 15:42.583
Fuck you.

15:42.583 --> 15:44.875
I'm sorry?

15:44.875 --> 15:46.875
[Daryll]
If you roll with us,

15:46.875 --> 15:49.125
you will get three of the best
in Los Angeles

15:49.125 --> 15:50.667
at crisis resolution.

15:50.667 --> 15:52.375
- He didn't count me.
- So what?

15:52.375 --> 15:54.417
Four fucking people work here.

15:54.417 --> 15:56.333
Not just three.

15:58.000 --> 16:01.083
[rap music playing]

16:01.083 --> 16:03.083
♪♪♪

16:03.083 --> 16:04.583
Fuck this.

16:04.583 --> 16:05.458
What's going on, Bunch?

16:05.458 --> 16:08.083
- Daryll's not counting me.
- What?

16:08.083 --> 16:10.709
And Lena, bossing me around
with paper and fucking coffee.

16:10.709 --> 16:12.458
Jesus fucking...

16:12.458 --> 16:15.125
I moved my family back
from Pismo Beach for you, Ray.

16:15.125 --> 16:17.417
[Bunchy]
I'm here to help you.

16:17.417 --> 16:19.250
I know you did, Bunch.

16:19.250 --> 16:20.875
All right.

16:20.875 --> 16:23.125
Well, I'ma be a luchador.

16:23.125 --> 16:24.417
What?

16:24.417 --> 16:26.417
El Trebol.

16:26.417 --> 16:27.875
What the fuck does that mean?

16:27.875 --> 16:28.834
"The Shamrock."

16:28.834 --> 16:32.375
Three weeks, ten cities.

16:32.375 --> 16:34.417
