34:00.959 --> 34:02.834
And the hunter thought,

34:02.834 --> 34:06.542
Well, this creature must be
the fiercest creature

34:06.542 --> 34:08.625
he will ever encounter.

34:08.625 --> 34:09.667
When he got to the village, he--

34:09.667 --> 34:12.333
he built a-a blind

34:12.333 --> 34:14.834
right at the edge
of the trees.

34:14.834 --> 34:16.583
And he waited.

34:16.583 --> 34:19.583
He was terrified.
He--he felt vulnerable.

34:19.583 --> 34:21.125
I mean, what kind
of creature was this

34:21.125 --> 34:24.041
that could kill 25 men
and never be stopped?

34:24.041 --> 34:27.208
Night came,
and as the hunter

34:27.208 --> 34:30.417
looked out into the bush,

34:30.417 --> 34:33.083
he didn't realize
that behind him

34:33.083 --> 34:35.291
the villagers
had gathered up their goats

34:35.291 --> 34:38.208
inside their huts
to keep them safe.

34:38.208 --> 34:40.375
But then there
wasn't enough room

34:40.375 --> 34:41.792
for everyone to sleep,

34:41.792 --> 34:45.875
so they pushed
the elderly outside...

34:45.875 --> 34:48.583
for the lion, you see.

34:48.583 --> 34:52.792
For the lion.

34:52.792 --> 34:54.625
Cheers.

34:54.625 --> 34:56.834
Cheers.

34:59.709 --> 35:00.834
Do you think
that there's a moral

35:00.834 --> 35:04.667
to this story, Mr. Donovan?

35:04.667 --> 35:06.291
I don't know.

35:06.291 --> 35:08.041
Don't get old.

35:08.041 --> 35:10.041
Don't get pushed out.

35:13.250 --> 35:14.333
Thanks for the drink.

35:18.083 --> 35:21.583
Did you meet my stepson?

35:21.583 --> 35:22.250
Who?

35:22.250 --> 35:25.125
George.
When you came in.

35:25.125 --> 35:26.458
Yeah.

35:26.458 --> 35:26.917
He doesn't drive.

35:26.917 --> 35:29.792
He needs a lift.

35:29.792 --> 35:31.625
Do you mind?

35:33.667 --> 35:36.083
Sure.

35:39.667 --> 35:41.667
[door opens]

35:41.667 --> 35:43.750
♪ dramatic music ♪

35:43.750 --> 35:49.625
♪♪♪

35:52.792 --> 35:56.875
[exhales deeply]

36:00.625 --> 36:03.250
You ready?

36:03.250 --> 36:06.625
Okay, marido,  let's do this.

36:12.041 --> 36:17.250
♪ And in the end... ♪

36:17.250 --> 36:20.667
♪ And in the... ♪

36:32.417 --> 36:35.959
You ever been to that hotel
in Culver City

36:35.959 --> 36:38.834
where all
the Munchkins stayed

36:38.834 --> 36:43.333
when they were working
on The Wizard of Oz?

36:43.333 --> 36:44.500
No.

36:44.500 --> 36:47.417
[cell phone ringing]

36:47.959 --> 36:51.500
[cell phone beeps]

36:51.500 --> 36:52.792
Yeah.

36:52.792 --> 36:55.250
[Terry]
We got to talk.

36:55.250 --> 36:56.709
What's up, Ter?

36:56.709 --> 36:58.709
It's fucking important.

36:58.709 --> 37:00.709
I can't talk right now.

37:00.709 --> 37:02.959
Yeah, well...

37:02.959 --> 37:05.417
it's fucking important.

37:05.417 --> 37:07.041
Where are you?

37:07.041 --> 37:09.542
I'm in the club.

37:09.542 --> 37:11.208
[cell phone beeps]

37:11.208 --> 37:12.625
Yeah, so...

37:12.625 --> 37:16.625
that's where all
the little people stayed

37:16.625 --> 37:19.959
when--when they were
doing the movie.

37:19.959 --> 37:22.917
There was, like,
drunken Munchkin orgies.

37:22.917 --> 37:26.041
One little fella--
he killed himself on set.

37:26.041 --> 37:27.917
[George] You can--you can
see it in the movie.

37:27.917 --> 37:29.542
There's a little guy, like,

37:29.542 --> 37:32.041
hanging from the tree
in the Tin Man scene.

37:32.041 --> 37:33.792
♪ Mazzy Star's "Fade Into You" ♪

37:33.792 --> 37:36.750
♪ The strange light
comes on slowly ♪

37:36.750 --> 37:41.458
♪♪♪

37:41.458 --> 37:45.208
♪ A stranger's heart
is out of home... ♪

37:45.208 --> 37:46.333
Your heart's pounding.

37:46.333 --> 37:47.417
- Is it?
- Yeah.

37:47.417 --> 37:50.083
- [inhales deeply]
- What's going on?

37:50.083 --> 37:51.750
[exhales deeply]
Nothing.

37:51.750 --> 37:55.458
I feel good.

37:55.458 --> 37:59.250
- I think.
- [chuckles]

37:59.250 --> 38:02.291
Barely recognize it, huh?

38:02.291 --> 38:05.375
♪ Cover your heart ♪

38:05.375 --> 38:07.875
♪♪♪

38:07.875 --> 38:09.125
Abs...

38:09.125 --> 38:10.667
♪ Fade into you... ♪

38:10.667 --> 38:14.667
- What do you want to do?
- I could go for a burger.

38:14.667 --> 38:16.625
No, I mean, you know...

38:16.625 --> 38:18.417
[breathes deeply]

38:18.417 --> 38:22.083
Now that the kids
are leaving the house and...

38:22.083 --> 38:22.792
we're getting older.

38:22.792 --> 38:27.041
♪♪♪

38:27.041 --> 38:29.291
I'm not getting older.

38:29.291 --> 38:33.792
Seriously.

38:33.792 --> 38:36.333
If you could do
anything you want,

38:36.333 --> 38:37.834
what would it be?

38:37.834 --> 38:38.959
- Anything?
- Yeah.

38:38.959 --> 38:43.875
♪♪♪

38:45.041 --> 38:47.834
Maybe open a bar?

38:47.834 --> 38:49.375
A bar?

38:49.375 --> 38:49.750
Yeah.

38:49.750 --> 38:52.542
[scoffs]

38:52.542 --> 38:55.208
It'd be someplace
for the family to get together

38:55.208 --> 38:59.417
and someplace
for Bunchy to work...

38:59.417 --> 39:01.000
and Conor.

39:01.000 --> 39:02.875
God knows he's gonna need a job.

39:02.875 --> 39:04.709
[chuckles]

39:04.709 --> 39:05.709
Abs,

39:05.709 --> 39:08.875
you left Boston to get
away from running a bar.

39:08.875 --> 39:12.000
[laughing]

39:12.000 --> 39:14.333
I'm drunk.

39:14.333 --> 39:18.208
You asked me
what I wanted, and...

39:18.208 --> 39:20.500
♪♪♪

39:20.500 --> 39:23.417
I don't know--
it would just...

39:23.417 --> 39:25.875
It would remind me
of home, you know?

39:25.875 --> 39:27.834
[chuckles]

39:27.834 --> 39:30.291
♪♪♪

39:30.291 --> 39:32.375
Ray!
[gasps]

39:32.375 --> 39:35.458
♪ dramatic music ♪

39:35.458 --> 39:40.375
♪♪♪

39:40.375 --> 39:42.500
[crashing]

39:48.375 --> 39:51.375
[loud crash]

39:51.375 --> 39:55.542
♪♪♪

39:59.375 --> 40:01.542
[both breathing heavily]

40:04.625 --> 40:07.125
You okay?

40:07.125 --> 40:10.959
[breathing heavily]

40:10.959 --> 40:12.500
Yeah.

40:12.500 --> 40:14.834
You got a little bump
on your head.

40:14.834 --> 40:16.291
All right.

40:16.291 --> 40:17.458
Can you move?

40:17.458 --> 40:19.667
- Yeah.
- Okay.

40:19.667 --> 40:22.667
[Mazzy Star's "Fade into You"
continues playing on car radio]

40:22.667 --> 40:27.542
♪♪♪

40:36.834 --> 40:39.917
♪ tender ambient music ♪

40:39.917 --> 40:44.792
♪♪♪

40:54.291 --> 40:56.291
[George]
Oh, of course,

40:56.291 --> 40:59.709
now they've mastered out the--
the little dead guy.

40:59.709 --> 41:01.709
But you can't erase
things like that

41:01.709 --> 41:03.041
from people's minds.

41:03.041 --> 41:04.875
You can't.

41:04.875 --> 41:07.500
Once you see horrible things,

41:07.500 --> 41:09.625
you can't erase them.

41:09.625 --> 41:13.291
I-I saw my sister die.

41:16.542 --> 41:17.667
What?

41:21.208 --> 41:23.291
"Home is where the heart is."

41:23.291 --> 41:25.667
That's what Dorothy said.

41:28.458 --> 41:32.083
"There's no place like home."

41:32.083 --> 41:35.208
Exactly.

41:35.208 --> 41:37.625
Exactly.
That's my point.

41:41.750 --> 41:43.041
[roars]

41:43.041 --> 41:44.625
[Bunchy]
Come on, baby!

41:44.625 --> 41:46.417
[grunts]

41:46.417 --> 41:48.834
- [man moaning oddly]
- [chuckles]

41:49.917 --> 41:52.458
Shit!

41:52.458 --> 41:55.041
[Bunchy] Come on.
Come on, get them! Let's go!

41:55.041 --> 41:57.333
No! No!

42:00.542 --> 42:04.291
[shouting oddly]

42:04.291 --> 42:06.417
[Bunchy groaning]

42:06.417 --> 42:10.417
[people]
shouting in Spanish

42:13.917 --> 42:14.333
[man] shouts in Spanish

42:14.333 --> 42:16.375
Oh, shit.

42:16.375 --> 42:19.417
- Um...
- [man groaning]

42:19.417 --> 42:22.709
El Tigre.
Kevin.

42:22.709 --> 42:24.875
- Oh, fuck.
- [man] shouting in Spanish

42:24.875 --> 42:27.959
- [breathing heavily]
- [man groaning]

42:31.333 --> 42:32.166
[man] Ayúdalo.

42:32.166 --> 42:36.083
[thunder rumbles]

42:41.709 --> 42:43.125
Ter?

42:46.375 --> 42:49.208
♪ Andy Kim's "Rock Me Gently" ♪

42:49.208 --> 42:51.709
♪♪♪

42:51.709 --> 42:53.792
[Andy Kim]
♪ Ain't it good? ♪

42:53.792 --> 42:55.333
♪ Ain't it right ♪

42:55.333 --> 42:56.417
♪ That you are with me ♪

42:56.417 --> 42:59.542
♪ Here tonight? ♪

42:59.542 --> 43:01.417
♪ Music playing ♪

43:01.417 --> 43:03.625
♪ Our bodies swaying in time ♪

43:03.625 --> 43:07.000
[female chorus]
♪ In time, in time, in time ♪

43:07.000 --> 43:09.166
[Andy Kim]
♪ Touching you ♪

43:09.166 --> 43:10.667
♪ So warm and tender ♪

43:10.667 --> 43:15.625
♪ Lord, I feel
such a sweet surrender ♪

43:15.625 --> 43:19.375
♪ Beautiful is the dream
that makes you mine ♪

43:19.375 --> 43:20.917
♪♪♪

43:20.917 --> 43:21.750
[female chorus]
♪ Mmm ♪

43:21.750 --> 43:24.750
[Andy Kim]
♪ Rock me gently ♪

43:24.750 --> 43:26.750
♪ Rock me slowly ♪

43:26.750 --> 43:28.583
♪ Take it easy ♪

43:28.583 --> 43:30.041
♪ Don't you know ♪

43:30.041 --> 43:31.583
♪ That I have never been ♪

43:31.583 --> 43:36.166
